DevOps Real-time Project: K8s A-z Mastery
Deploying Kubernetes on AWS using Kubeadm: End-to-End Setup
________________________________________
Project Overview
In this project, we will deploy a Kubernetes cluster on Amazon Web Services (AWS) using kubeadm. Since kubeadm does not provision resources, we will first set up the required infrastructure on AWS, including virtual machines, networking, and security groups. Then, we will install kubeadm, initialize the Kubernetes master node, join worker nodes, and configure networking.
________________________________________
Project Roadmap
Step 1: Provision AWS Infrastructure
âœ… Create EC2 Instances
â€¢	Log in to AWS Management Console.
â€¢	Navigate to EC2 > Launch Instance and create three EC2 instances:
o	1 Master Node (t2.medium, Ubuntu 20.04)
o	2 Worker Nodes (t2.medium, Ubuntu 20.04)
â€¢	Create a security group (k8s-sg) with the following rules:
o	Port 22 (SSH) â€“ Allow access from your IP
o	Port 6443 (Kubernetes API Server) â€“ Allow from worker nodes
o	Port 10250, 10255 (Kubelet API) â€“ Allow from all cluster nodes
o	Port 179 (Calico networking) â€“ Allow from all cluster nodes
o	Port 2379-2380 (etcd) â€“ Allow from master and workers
âœ… Attach IAM Role (Optional)
â€¢	Create an IAM role with AmazonEC2FullAccess for Kubernetes to manage EC2 resources.
